        <content>
          <p>TITLE XXI
INSANITY PROCEEDINGS
CHAPTER 1.  MENTAL INCAPACITY TO PROCEED
Art. 641.  Mental incapacity to proceed defined
Mental incapacity to proceed exists when, as a result of mental disease or defect, a defendant presently lacks the capacity to understand the proceedings against him or to assist in his defense.</p>
